# Build the retro writer

## Step

Resolved when: (1) an Inngest event (e.g. `memory/retro.requested`)
carrying pointers (brief path, session id, repo) triggers a condenser
function that reads the closed brief + its steps' Result sections and
writes one retro `.svx` into the retros store the curator reads
(`dark-wizard/.brain/resources/retros/`); (2) claude/codex/pi hooks can
fire that event on demand (hook wiring documented; at minimum a
one-liner CLI/script an agent can call at effort close); (3) the noise
bar from the [decision](../memory-system-repair/decide-retro-writer.svx)
is enforced: retros only for efforts with real decisions or multi-step
work, and the output must say what changed durable behavior, not
re-narrate the ledger; (4) one real retro exists as proof — generated
from the closed
[memory-system-review brief](../memory-system-review/memory-system-review-brief.svx).
Serialized behind the retirement migration (same repo surface).
